      <p>
        Prawn Bhuna is a popular dish in the Indian subcontinent, particularly in Bangladesh and India.
        The word 'bhuna' means to cook on low heat until the spices are well roasted and the dish is rich in flavour.
        The origins of Prawn Bhuna can be traced back to the Mughal era in India. The Mughal emperors were known for their love of rich and flavorful foods, 
        and their influence can be seen in many traditional Indian/Bengali dishes, including Prawn Bhuna.
    </p>

