    <div class="ingredients">
      <h3>For more information, please click on the ingredients</h3>
          <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
      <p>
          <ul>500g Prawns peeled and deveined</ul>

          <ul>2 finely chopped Onions</ul>
      
          <ul>2 finely chopped Tomatoes</ul>
      
          <ul>2-3 chopped <a href="green_chili">Green Chillies</a></ul>

          <ul>1 tsp <a href="ginger">Ginger Paste</a></ul>

          <ul>1 tsp <a href="garlic">Garlic Paste</a></ul>

          <ul>1 tsp <a href="cumin">Cumin Powder</a></ul>

          <ul>1 tsp <a href="coriander">Coriander Powder</a></ul>

          <ul>1/2 tsp <a href="turmeric">Turmeric Powder</a></ul>

          <ul>1 tsp <a href="red_chili_powder">Red Chili Powder</a></ul>

          <ul>Salt to taste</ul>

          <ul>2 tbsp Vegetable Oil</ul>

          <ul>Fresh Corriander to garnish</ul>

          <br>

      </p>

    </div>

    <div class="instructions">
      <h2>Instructions:</h2>
      
      <p>
        <ol type="1">
        <li>Heat the oil in a pan and add the chopped onions. Saut√© until the onions turn golden brown. 
           </li>
           <br>

        <li>Add the ginger and garlic paste and fry for a minute.
            </li>
            <br>

        <li>Add the chopped tomatoes and green chillies and fry for 2-3 minutes until the tomatoes are soft.
            </li>
            <br>

        <li>Add the cumin, coriander, turmeric, red chilli powder and salt. Fry for a minute until the spices are well mixed.
          </li>
          <br>

        <li>Add the prawns and stir well so that the prawns are coated with the spices. Cook for 5-7 minutes until the prawns are cooked through.
          </li>
          <br>

        <li>Garnish with coriander leaves and serve hot with rice or naan.
          </li>
          <br>
      
      </ol><br>

    </p>
